name: Puja Mandala
address: Jalan Nusa Dua, Kuta Selatan, Benoa, Kec. Kuta Sel., Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1:
It's nice to visit a place in Bali where all religions coexist in peace and harmony. All major faith and religions are represented in one strip. A mosque stands next to a Catholic church, next to a Buddhist temple, next to a Protestant church next to Hindu temple.

This place is a testament to Bali's promotion of respect to all faith and religion.
review 2: Amazing place in Nusa Dua where different religious buildings in one place side by side. Hindu temple, Christian church, Buddhist temple and Muslim  mosque. There are moderate dress codes to enter the temples ( we visited the Hindu temple and Buddhist temple ) needs to cover legs if you wear short pants. We visited during weekday and not many people there. It is free to visit ( no entry fees).
review 3: Great to see all the world religions peacefully side by side. Good example of Balinese openess and welcoming atmosphere! Dont forget to weer appropriate clothing.
review 4: This is a place where religions co-exist, you have a mosque, Buddhist temple, Catholic Church all on one site, and you can visit each of them and pray or just explore. At the temple, women need to be covered up so wear a long dress. I was given a wrap as a had on a summer dress that was above my knees.
review 5: A worship complex of all religion in Indonesia. You can pray at a place according to your religion. This complex is huge with more huge parking. Many jumah prayers on Friday noon. Avoid the time if you want less people. This place is also nice for pictures. We love it

name: Masjid Agung Ibnu Batutah
address: Jl. Nusa Dua, Kuta, Kec. Kuta Sel., Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1:
I go to this mosque quite often if I'm around the Nusa Dua area. This is my favourite mosque!

The parking lot is huge because it is shared with other religious sites. But, they also have a large field dedicated to the tourists and their buses.

The mosque is clean and comfortable, especially after being renovated. It is quite cold during the evening prayer.

The toilets and the abolition place are clean and spacious.
review 2: Beautiful masjid. Jummah time is 1210. It was great to see a temple both Hindu and Buddhist along with the church in the same complex. Shows solidarity and mutual respect Indonesian people have for other religions.
review 3:
Masha-Allah. Beautiful masjid. Prayed Jumah today iat around 12:20pm on Sept 8th, 2023.
I have travelled quite a bit around the world. So far I have never seen a mosque, a Church, a Buddhist Temple, a Hindu Temple all besides each other.
Subhan-Allah. Shows unity with each other‚Äôs regardless of religious beliefs, race, color and gender. I‚Äôm impressed :-)
review 4: It was very beautiful and very moderate and tolerated society .The church, besides it, allows us to park during the friday prayer.
review 5: This Mosque is Charming, large, clean and easy access. If you came from Nusadua, Jimbaran, Pandawa Beach, Tanjung Benoa this mosque is great to stop by for praying ( sholat ). Such a peaceful place.

review 1:
cozy and nice villa. for sure, everyone would enjoy staying here.
well, i wish the wifi connection can be stronger tho, so the rooms on the second floor could also enjoy using the internet. and also, hopefully the bidet in every toilet can get a bit stronger.
review 2: Discover the charm of a great villa in the heart of Nusa Dua! If you appreciate peace, convenience, immersing yourself with the locals and nature, this is the ideal holiday spot. During our 8-day stay, the facilities and service were top-notch. Plus, everything is at your doorstep, and if you enjoy walking, the beach is just a half-hour stroll away! üòäüå¥üè°
review 3:
Generally the villa was comfortable and nice the only thing i didnt like and i pay for it the breakfast there is no choices and uncontrollable only two choices queen and king
And there was near by noise area also there big gecko scary ones and doing some noise
review 4:
It definitely lived up to the pictures as advertised! We felt very welcomed and their hospitality was top notch!! They were always helpful and even brought our GRAB food that we ordered to our room door when we were a bit late to pick them up.

In terms of the room and its cleanliness, we would rate it 8.5 - 9 out of 10. As it is exposed to nature, one cannot run away from lizard droppings as there were about 5-6, which is understandable. A little freshener might also help, to give a nice smell upon entering the villa.

Nevertheless, I will definitely come and stay again in future - for the vibrant employees and the hospitality showcased. Thank you for having us üôè
review 5: To be honest, I didn't like the location as much,but this place is absolutely worth every penny. Love it.

name: Bali Villa 4U
address: Unnamed Road, Benoa, Benoa, Kuta Sel, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1:
Excellent location, hospitality and amenities. Thank you Bali Villa 4U!

Had a beautiful stay at Bali Villa 4U. Hosts Peter and Chrissie were always available for support and suggestions to make our holiday worry-free and as comfortable as possible. Housekeeper Ayu and Guide Wayan were also excellent. This was our first trip to Bali and we appreciated all the local knowledge and recommendations that were shared. We would definitely stay here again. Thank you!
review 2:
Bali villa 4U is the best villa that I saw in this district. I think it is the best value for money!
Villa has all items for comfortable holidays, a big swimming pool, 3 huge bedrooms with king-size beds, a massage table, a perfect kitchen with a spacious fridge and different kitchen equipment. The room on the second floor has a beautiful view. The leaving room is great with smart TV and a great sound system! Honestly, often we didn't want to leave the villa and we had dinner at home. Also, instead go to a beach we preferred to stay at the villa's swimming pool :)
Regarding the atmosphere and comfortable in the room: there is air conditions in each room, but I was afraid to get cold and tried didn't use it, but 2 rooms have panoramic doors to 2 sides it is allowed to make a draft with fresh air. So, I strongly recommended this villa!
Also, about owners, Peter and Chrissie is very hospitable and helpfully. I think Peter can solve any question in Bali and He can give tons of helpful advice about places and services. I was surprised by their goodness and openness.
review 3:
A fantastic place for a family getaway! All the family enjoyed our time spent at this spacious villa. The young ones loved the private pool. The beds were comfy and the living area was big enough for all six of us to share in comfort. Peter and Chrissy are fantastic hosts and went out of their way to make all the family feel at home and make our stay very memorable.
Even organised a birthday cake then delivered it to the restaurant for us!
review 4: My husband and 2 friends of ours stayed in the villa for 13 nights. It is a spacious, fully equipped villa with a private pool, truly magnificent. The beds were very comfortable and it was serviced each day by Nyoman and Made, who were always so polite and friendly. Wayan, our driver, was excellent, knows Bali very well and was always so very accommodating. It was our first time in Bali and we all say thank you to Peter and Chrissie, they were so helpful and considerate that when our trip came to an end, it felt like we were parting with friends.
review 5:
This is Villa is amazing. Beyond words can describe. I loved my overall experience in Bali at this Villa. It helped me get into holiday mood real quick hehe.
The Villa is beautifully private, spacious and catered to my every need plus more. The staff are friendly and kind hearted. To the owners you guys are amazing and you helped make my first trip in Bali feel so enjoyable. I definetly recommend this place to anyone and everyone.
